  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Rearrange the array\n\nWrite a program to convert the array in such a way that double its value and replace the next number with 0 if current and next element are same and rearrange the array such that all 0's shifted to the end.\n\n\n\nFor Example\n\nThe given array is: 0 3 3 3 0 0 7 7 0 9\n\nThe new array is: 6 3 14 9 0 0 0 0 0 0\n\nExplanation:\n\n   In the given array the second and third element is equal hence hence double the first 3 and make the next index value as 0. The element which which is in third index doesn't have any match so leave as it is. finally move all zero to the end",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 100",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 1000"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The input contains an integer N which is the size of the array and in the array and in the next line N elements will be there",
    "outputFormat": "Print the updated array with the space",
